verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Come, Lord, and tarry not;
Bring the long looked for day;
O why these years of waiting here,
These ages of decay?{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Come, for Thy saints still wait;
Daily ascends their sigh;
The Spirit and the Bride say, Come;
Does Thou not hear the cry?{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Come, for the good are few;
They lift the voice in vain;
Faith waxes fainter on the earth,
And love is on the wane.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Come, for love waxes cold,
Its steps are faint and slow;
Faith now is lost in unbelief,
Hope’s lamp burns dim and low.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Come, and make all things new,
Build up this ruined earth;
Restore our faded paradise,
Creation’s second birth.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Come, and begin Thy reign
Of everlasting peace;
Come, take the kingdom to Thyself,
Great King of righteousness.{/lang-eng}
